# Improve documentation

## Link 

https://supabase.com/docs/guides/getting-started/tutorials/with-angular

## Describe the problem

The Angular tutorial's Auth component implementation contains a TypeScript error. The code example shows FormBuilder being used before initialization, which will cause compilation errors for developers following the tutorial.

## Describe the improvement

The code example should be updated to initialize the form group in the constructor. This follows Angular's best practices and prevents the TypeScript initialization error.

Before:
```typescript
export class AuthComponent {
  loading = false
  signInForm = this.formBuilder.group({
    email: '',
  })
  constructor(
    private readonly supabase: SupabaseService,
    private readonly formBuilder: FormBuilder
  ) {}
```

After:
```typescript
export class AuthComponent {
  loading = false;
  signInForm;

  constructor(
    private readonly supabase: SupabaseService,
    private readonly formBuilder: FormBuilder
  ) {
    this.signInForm = this.formBuilder.group({
      email: '',
    });
  }
```
## Additional context
When following the current tutorial, developers will encounter this TypeScript error:
> Property 'formBuilder' is used before being initialized.

If there are any mistakes in the code after the improvement, please tell me!

