### Description

Messages received from OpenAI models include `itemId`s in `providerOptions` for message content parts. For Zero Data Retention organizations, OpenAI will error when receiving `itemId` in messages. It's reasonable for us to handle filtered these out in messages sent to future model calls, but it would be nice to have some way to have the library do this for us.

Note the example tries to result in a tool call, but the tool isn't actually used and tool calls aren't necessary to reproduce the error.

```ts
import { openai } from "@ai-sdk/openai";
import { generateText, tool } from "ai";
import { z } from "zod";

async function main() {
  const model = openai('gpt-5');

  console.log('Asking for tool call...');
  const { response } = await generateText({
    model,
    prompt: 'Call `main_tool`',
    tools: {
        main_tool: tool({
            description: 'Main tool',
            inputSchema: z.object({
                name: z.string(),
            }),
            execute: async ({ name }) => {
                return `Hello, ${name}!`;
            },
        }),
    }
  });
  console.log('Response messages:');
  console.log(JSON.stringify(response.messages, null, 2));

  console.log('Generating second response...');
  const { response: secondResponse } = await generateText({
    model,
    messages: response.messages,
  });
  console.log('Second response messages:');
  console.log(JSON.stringify(secondResponse.messages, null, 2));
}

main().catch(console.error);
```

